To create fancy social media icons, you can use HTML and CSS, potentially incorporating libraries like Font Awesome for icon fonts or SVG icons. You can customize the appearance with CSS, adding effects like hover states, rounded corners, and color changes to make them visually appealing. [1, 1, 2, 2, 3, 3, 4, 5]  
Here's a breakdown of how to approach this: 
1. Include a CSS Library (Optional but Recommended): [1, 1, 6]  

• Font Awesome: A popular library that provides a wide range of icons as fonts. 
• How to use it: 
	• Link to the Font Awesome CSS file in your HTML &lt;head&gt;: [1, 1, 7, 8, 9]  

        <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/4.7.0/css/font-awesome.min.css">

• Use the icons in your HTML using their respective class names (e.g., fa fa-facebook for the Facebook icon). [1]  

2. Create HTML Structure: 

• Use &lt;a&gt; tags for clickable icons that link to your social media profiles. [1]  
• Wrap the icons in a &lt;ul&gt; list for better organization (optional). [3]  

    <ul class="social-media-list">
        <li><a href="#" class="fa fa-facebook"></a></li>
        <li><a href="#" class="fa fa-twitter"></a></li>
        <li><a href="#" class="fa fa-instagram"></a></li>
    </ul>

3. Style with CSS: 

• Basic styling: 
	• Set font sizes, padding, and text decoration: 

        .fa {
            padding: 20px;
            font-size: 30px;
            width: 50px;
            text-align: center;
            text-decoration: none;
        }

Add hover effects. 
        .fa:hover {
            opacity: 0.7;
        }

• Set specific colors for different icons (using the brand colors): 

        .fa-facebook {
            background: #3B5998;
            color: white;
        }

• Advanced styling: 
	• Add rounded corners using border-radius: 

        .fa {
            border-radius: 50%; /* or any other value */
        }

